Mapfluence Session Notes
Date: 2026-03-18

User workflow preferences
- Commit and push to `main` after completed code changes until the user says otherwise.
- Keep practical, restart-safe notes in this `.mb` file.
- Prefer concise Ask Mapfluence AI responses by default (short summary + non-redundant short bullets).
- `/hastings/technical` should behave like a selected-user tool without admin/non-admin gating in the UI; full technical assessment features (including cloud save) should be available there.

Current Hastings map architecture target
- Admin full map: `/:universityId/admin` (Mapfluence edit + AI + planning tools).
- Admin combined stakeholder + technical: `/:universityId/admin/engagement`.
- Public stakeholder engagement: `/:universityId/engagement`.
- Public technical assessment: `/:universityId/technical`.

Latest completed work (2026-04-03 mapbox token prompt removal)
- Reopened troubleshooting for new-user browsers being asked for a Mapbox token.
- Confirmed StakeholderMap.jsx still had a browser token modal path even with tokenless fallback present.
- Removed token modal state, save handler, and modal UI so users are no longer prompted to enter a token in-browser.
- Preserved tokenless map init fallback to OpenStreetMap when no public token is available.
- Changed map access-token error path to warning logs only (no blocking prompt).
- Environment note: Node.js/npm are not installed in this shell, so local build validation could not run in-session.

Latest completed work (2026-03-30 planner copilot practical floor-first recovery)
- Added practical floor-first recovery controls to strict copilot runs.
- Client now passes `practicalFloorFirstOnStrictMiss=true` and `practicalNearRangeTolerance=0.12` for strict copilot requests.
- Server strict-fallback ranking now prefers near-range options inside the practical band (+/-12%) before emergency nearest-fit fallback when strict +/-5% options are unavailable.
- Added explicit assumption/criteria notes in output so this fallback behavior is transparent to planners.
- Validation completed: `node --check ai-server/server.js` and `npm.cmd run build`.

Latest completed work (2026-03-30 planner copilot hardening)
- Hardened `Create planning scenario` copilot flow to avoid strict-fit dead-end failures.
- Removed strict one-building hard-stop throw so one-building strict runs can still return closest options.
- Relaxed strict fallback acceptance and added emergency closest-fit fallback passes (with explicit under-target warnings) so strict mode returns a best-effort option instead of only erroring.
- In `StakeholderMap`, strict dead-end errors now auto-trigger one relaxed retry.
- Relaxed retry now disables academic-fit low-fit pruning so fallback runs actually broaden inventory.
- Validation completed: `node --check ai-server/server.js` and `npm.cmd run build`.

Latest completed work (2026-03-30 planner copilot floor-first strict tuning)
- Tightened strict fallback guardrail so weak underfilled options are less likely to win (`~80%` minimum strict fallback coverage before emergency fallback).
- Changed strict fallback selection to evaluate and rank multiple relax passes together instead of accepting the first weak nearest-fit option.
- Added contiguous floor-block fallback pass to better target “entire floor or near-floor” outcomes when strict in-range options are unavailable.
- Fixed relax-pass room sourcing so support/public relax passes can actually expand candidate inventory (previously still constrained by earlier filtering).
- Added fallback ranking preference for floor concentration and logged best fallback SF-gap notes for transparency.
- Validation completed: `node --check ai-server/server.js` and `npm.cmd run build`.

Latest completed work (2026-03-30 planner copilot floor-first fallback stage)
- Added an explicit floor-first fallback generator (`buildFloorBlockFallbackOptions`) that builds candidates from contiguous floor blocks (single-floor and same-building two-floor blends) before scattered room-level fallback.
- Integrated floor-first fallback passes in strict failure handling (`Auto-relax FB1` / `Auto-relax FB2`) so strict dead-end recovery can still surface whole-floor/near-floor options.
- Updated client-side criteria display so local hard-exclusion notes are suppressed when selected fallback output indicates relaxed family allowances were used, reducing contradictory messaging.
- Validation completed: `node --check ai-server/server.js` and `npm.cmd run build`.

Latest completed work (2026-03-30 planner copilot inventory bottleneck fix)
- Confirmed with live inventory diagnostics that viable strict one-building fits can exist in full data while UI results still underfit.
- Root cause: client-side copilot inventory downsampling/trim was too aggressive before server scoring.
- Increased copilot-mode inventory caps and trim ceilings in `onCreateMoveScenario` (campus room intake, fallback row intake, maxTotal/maxPerBuilding/maxPerType, and baseline trim per-type limits) so solver sees enough candidate space.
- Kept standard mode trim behavior unchanged.
- Validation completed: `node --check ai-server/server.js` and `npm.cmd run build`.

