Critical incident resolved (2026-04-06): first-time users seeing blank map on Hastings demo
- Impact:
  - New users in Firefox/Edge/Incognito were seeing a blank map and token errors.
  - Existing Chrome sessions sometimes worked due to prior local browser state.
- Primary symptom logs:
  - Mapbox token length: 0
  - Mapbox access token error: A valid Mapbox access token is required...
  - Uncaught ReferenceError: pk is not defined (when token script was added without quotes)
- Root cause chain:
  - Runtime token resolution depends on valid pk. token from env/runtime/local storage.
  - Fresh browser profiles had no local token.
  - A temporary HTML token injection was initially malformed (missing string quotes), causing pk is not defined and token length remained 0.
- Recovery that worked:
  - Added token via GitHub web edit in index.html with correct JS string syntax:
    - window.__MAPBOX_PUBLIC_TOKEN__ = 'pk....';
  - Verified map render recovery after deploy cache-bust (?v=...).
- Important operator notes:
  - GitHub Actions secret edit page intentionally shows blank value after save; this is normal.
  - Repo URL is case-sensitive: correct repo is JGD1130/StakeholderMap (not stakeholder-map).
  - Token must be public Mapbox token (pk...), not secret token (sk...).
- Cross-browser go-live checklist (use for all demos):
  1) Test in Chrome Incognito, Firefox Private, and Edge InPrivate.
  2) Confirm console does NOT show Mapbox token length: 0.
  3) Confirm map tiles render at https://jgd1130.github.io/StakeholderMap/hastings.
  4) Use cache-bust query param after deploy (?v=8 or newer).

Local hardening prepared in workspace (pending commit/deploy if desired):
- src/components/StakeholderMap.jsx
  - Hardened token normalizer to recover from common formatting mistakes:
    - quoted tokens
    - VITE_MAPBOX_PUBLIC_TOKEN=pk... format
    - extraction of pk... token substring
- .github/workflows/deploy.yml
  - Added build-time token validation step that fails when token is missing/invalid (pk. check).
